                           <extent>8</extent>
                        </quire>
                        <quire n="24">
                           <extent>8(-3)</extent>
                        </quire>
                        <quire n="25-26">
                           <extent>8</extent>
                        </quire>
                        <signatures>Gatherings signed, mid lower margin, first recto and
                           last verso, <foreign xml:lang="cu">е҃-л҃.</foreign>
                        </signatures>
                        <gregoryRule>Combination of FH HF FH HF FH HF FH HF and HF FH HF
                           FH HF FH HF FH, except for gatherings I (FH FH FH FH HF HF
                           HF HF), X (FH FH HF FH HF HF HF), XVI (FH HF HF FH HF FH FH
                           HF), XXIII (HF FH FH HF FH HF HF FH).</gregoryRule>
                        <ruling>Leroy system 11, type 23D1.</ruling>
                        <pricking>Traces of pricking.</pricking>
                     </collation>
                     <condition>Fair. Four gatherings in the beginning, a few leaves after f.
                                1, a folio after f. 184, and a few leaves in the end are missing.
                                Ff. 31-31v, 71v, 138v are blank.</condition>
                  </supportDesc>
                  <layoutDesc>
                     <layout columns="1" writtenLines="22"/>
                  </layoutDesc>
               </objectDesc>
               <ink>Black; red for titles, initials and marginalia.</ink>
               <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="overview">Ornamental, of mediocre quality, made by the
                            scribe; yellow, ochre, orange, green, blue-green and red
                            palette.</decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="headpieces">
                     <list type="simple">
                        <item>
                           <locus target="../images/BL_Addms39625/MF 5 - MF 5 Add 39625_page_0036.jpg">f. 32:</locus> Pylae, c<dimensions unit="mm" type="headpieces">
                              <height>120</height>
                              <width>165 </width>
                           </dimensions>, of interlaced pattern composed of double-frame,
                                    intersecting circles, drawn by compass and outlined in red; the
                                    ovoid sections are filled in by S-shaped foliate branch of
                                    half-palmettes, while the small sectors between them are filled
                                    in with small palmette patterns; the white frames of the circles
                                    are decorated with dots; two vegetal stems with palmette endings
                                    are framing the pattern from above and below; a central palmette
                                    motif at the middle of the upper line.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 70:</locus>Narrow band; interlaced pattern, outlined in
                                    red, not coloured; stems with granules between the plaits and
                                    four endings of foliate branches with half-palmette
                                    leaves.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 72:</locus>Pylae, c<dimensions unit="mm" type="keadpieces">
                              <height>100</height>
                              <width>150</width>
                           </dimensions>; interlaced pattern composed of a sequence of
                                    framed circles, drawn by compass, criss-crossed by vegetal stems
                                    with palmette endings; the sectors of the circles filled in with
                                    a quatrefoil pattern; red outlines; a fine linear cross at the
                                    centre on the upper line; lower ending developing in a pattern
                                    of interlaced and palmette elements, representing a stylized
                                    Tree of Life.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 138:</locus>Band; interlaced pattern, outlined in red,
                                    not coloured, formed by a thorny stem; four half-palmette motifs
                                    for the endings.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 139:</locus>Band, c<dimensions unit="mm" type="headpieces">
                              <height>95</height>
                              <width>170 </width>
                           </dimensions> for the decorated field; interlaced pattern
                                    composed of stems forming a net; large endings of various
                                    palmette patterns; red outlines; a central palmette motif on
                                    top.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 195:</locus>Band, of interlaced pattern, outlined in
                                    red, not coloured; composed of broad thorny stems with four
                                    small endings of half-palmette motifs.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 206:</locus>Band; interlaced pattern, outlined in red,
                                    not coloured; the thorny stems form a braid; foliate endings on
                                    the right side.</item>
                     </list>
                  </decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="initials">Red outlines, filled in with green, ocher and red
                            colours.</decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="initials">
                     <p>Large initials: </p>
                     <list type="simple">
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 32:</locus>Interlaced, in the Balkan interlaced style,
                                    letter <foreign xml:lang="cu">З</foreign>, <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <dim>65</dim>
                           </dimensions> high (8 lines).</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 72:</locus>Jointed, letter <foreign xml:lang="cu">П</foreign>, <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <dim>45</dim>
                           </dimensions> high (5 lines), with black and ocher inner
                                    contours; stylized foliate extenders.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus>f. 139:</locus>Interlaced, in the Balkan interlaced style,
                                    letter <foreign xml:lang="cu">В</foreign>, <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <dim>75</dim>
                           </dimensions> high (9 lines), with white granules between the
                                    plaits.</item>
                     </list>
                  </decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="initials">
                     <p>Small initials: </p>
                     <p>Not decorated, with a
                                few exceptions, mainly letters <foreign xml:lang="cu">Ч</foreign>,
                                having simple vegetal ornament.</p>
                  </decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="marg">
                     <locus>f. 28:</locus>Insertion mark in the lower margin, in the form of
                            human hand, holding a tablet.</decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="titles">Display script, with simple decoration of granules
                            (or buds).</decoNote>
               </decoDesc>
               <bindingDesc>
                  <p>Blue velvet on boards, <dimensions unit="mm" type="binding">
                        <height>295</height>
                        <width>210</width>
                     </dimensions>, edges of pages are gilt.</p>
               </bindingDesc>
