                           <dim>4</dim>
                        </dimensions>
                        <dimensions unit="mm" type="scriptline">
                           <dim>8</dim>
                        </dimensions> on ff. 1-184v, 207-207v - for the Gospels text, the
                                end of the reading aparatus, and in smaller and more informal
                                semiuncial; <dimensions unit="mm" type="letters">
                           <dim>3</dim>
                        </dimensions>
                        <dimensions unit="mm" type="scriptline">
                           <dim>8</dim>
                        </dimensions> for the rest of the suplements on ff. 185-206v,
                                208-208v.</p>
                  </scriptDesc>
                  <scribeLang>
                     <orthography>
                        <p>Old Church Slavonic.</p>
                        <p>Two-<emph>jer</emph>, two-<emph>jus</emph> orthography, with
                                    confusion of <foreign xml:lang="cu">ѫ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="cu">ѧ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="cu">ы</foreign> and distinction between <foreign xml:lang="cu">з</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="cu">ѕ</foreign>.</p>
                     </orthography>
                  </scribeLang>
               </scribe>
            </scribeDesc>
            <msContents defective="false">
               <summary>For Gospels with Synaxarion and Menologion. The beginning and end are
                        missing, leaving Matthew 15:23-16:2, 16:21 - John 21:20. Mark, Luke and John
